                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="acidjazz_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a type of dance music that combines jazz, <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/funk_1" title="funk definition"><span class="ndv">funk</span></a>, <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/soul" title="soul definition"><span class="ndv">soul</span></a>, and <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/hip-hop" title="hip-hop definition"><span class="ndv">hip-hop</span></a></span></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" source="ald9_guide" id="acidjazz_unbox_1" unbox="cult"><span class="box_title">Culture</span><span class="body"><span class="p">Acid jazz was popular in the 1990s. Groups such as Incognito and the Brand New Heavies were typical of the style, using jazz instruments, <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/rap_1" title="rap definition"><span class="ndv">rap</span></a> singers and a fast rhythm.</span></span></span></div><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="acidjazz_unbox_2"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">apparently coined from <span class="eb">acid house</span> and popularized by the <span class="ei">Acid Jazz</span> record label founded in 1988.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
